<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="1489" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1489">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.12/24.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Brazilian Minister to
                                    Mexico</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-11">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 11, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>156. Your 79, July 8. Department has been pleased to instruct American
                            Consul General, Monterey, again urgently to bring to attention of
                            Constitutionalist Chief advisability of extending full protection to
                            persons connected with religious organizations.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">John E. Osborne.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>